The published BackendSet runtime keeps
request-path lookup under
pkg/servicemanager/loadbalancer/backendset by
resolving loadBalancerId from status or spec and
backendSetName from status.name or spec.name.
Create first probes GetBackendSet on the
deterministic backend set path; a matching
backend set binds into observe or update, while
a 404 falls through to list lookup by name and
then CreateBackendSet.
Create and update use read-after-write
follow-up, then settle through the next observe
because BackendSet payloads do not expose
lifecycle fields. Delete retains the finalizer
until GetBackendSet or list fallback confirms
the backend set is gone.
end note
